  <title translate="true">long filenames</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true">Long file names</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> are file and folder names that don&apos;t conform to the 8-character base, 3-character extension format that was once popular on PCs. Although Walls recognizes long file names and allows their use for folders and </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">project script files </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">(extension WPJ), it&apos;s a requirement that </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">survey data files </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">(extension SRV) have base names no longer than 8-characters. This restriction is due to compatibility concerns, field lengths in database tables, and the fact that Walls already maintains and displays fully descriptive </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">titles </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">for those survey files</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
